Popular Juju star Adeyinka Adeboye aka Boyebest has narrated his ordeals in the hands of police operatives while returning from Ibadan. The juju star, in an Instagram post, said the operatives threatened to kill him even after they had extorted him. Weeping profusely in the video, Boyebest said he couldn’t record the the whole scenario. He said: “Not Evn cos of the money they collected……what if they actually rush me. Into the bush like they threatened. They said they will kill me. They said they will put their hands inside my anus and I will pay millions. They collected a lots of money from me “What am I even saying? This is not different to kidnapping and robbery, and it was done by people that should be protecting us @nigeriapoliceforce. That i was so scared for my life is an understatement…… After ODEDA LOCAL GOVERNMENT, coming from ibadan   Clash on Lagos Island: We have made some arrests –…     Nothing can make me return to party politics –…     Please pray for my health, Olisa Metuh begs Nigerians   - Advertisement - “I couldn’t record cos they were careful, they collected my phones, and they look so scary……..one of them banging his teeth like he’s already feeling like killing me. Telling me I’m driving a nice car, is that crime? “I had to give them all money with me. Ahhhhh GOD! Lost of words. Short of words. Pls my people becareful on the road “@nigeriapoliceforce i so much have respect for this office and I was among the people that still believe things will eventually change for good. This experience Iv change my mind, not anymore. “I’m coming to your office @nigeriapoliceforce you have to take this up. This is not policing. What a day! What a country ……….” Police authorities were yet to respond to the allegations at the time of filing this report.